Title: Check your Council Tax balance and bills
Text: You can view your Council Tax bill and balance by signing in to the Bradford Council online account.

Title: Apply for a Council Tax discount or exemption
Text: You may be eligible for a discount or exemption (for example, single person discount or student exemption). Apply online and provide supporting evidence.

Title: Set up, change, or manage Council Tax direct debit
Text: You can pay Council Tax by direct debit, online card payment, or other payment methods.

Title: Tell the council you have moved home
Text: If you move home, tell the council your old and new address and your move date so your Council Tax is updated.

Title: Council Tax arrears, reminders, and enforcement
Text: If you have missed payments, pay what you can quickly and contact the Council Tax team to discuss an arrangement.

Title: Find your bin collection day
Text: Check your bin collection day using the council bin collection lookup by entering your postcode.

Title: Report a missed bin collection
Text: If your bin was not collected, check it was out on time and placed correctly, then report a missed collection online.

Title: Request a replacement bin
Text: If your bin is damaged or missing, you can request a replacement online. You may need your address and the bin type.

Title: What goes in recycling and what does not
Text: Recycling rules vary by area. Common items include paper, cardboard, and some plastics. Avoid contaminated items.

Title: Book a bulky waste collection
Text: You can book a bulky waste collection for large household items. Fees may apply depending on items and quantity.

Title: Check if you might be eligible for benefits support
Text: Eligibility depends on your circumstances (income, savings, household). Use guidance and calculators to understand options.

Title: Housing Benefit and Council Tax Support guidance
Text: You may qualify for Housing Benefit (if eligible) and/or Council Tax Support. Apply online and provide proof of income, rent, and identity.

Title: Report a change in circumstances
Text: Report changes (income, job, moving home, household changes) as soon as possible to avoid overpayments or delays.

Title: Universal Credit signposting
Text: Universal Credit is managed by the DWP. Claims and payments are handled via your Universal Credit online account.

Title: Help with urgent financial hardship
Text: If you are experiencing urgent hardship, check local welfare support, food support, and community services signposting.

Title: Apply for a school place (admissions)
Text: Apply for a school place via the council admissions portal. Check deadlines and provide required documents.

Title: Check school admissions deadlines
Text: Admissions deadlines depend on primary, secondary, or in-year applications. Check the council key dates page.

Title: In-year school transfers
Text: In-year transfers are available if you need to move schools during the year. Places depend on capacity and criteria.

Title: School transport guidance
Text: School transport support depends on age, distance, and eligibility. Check the council guidance for criteria and applications.

Title: Special Educational Needs and Disabilities (SEND) support
Text: Bradford Council provides SEND guidance, including assessment routes and EHCP information.
